Command Data Description <code>vol_set</code> <code>number</code> (0-100) Set audio volume <code>vol_mute</code> -- Toggle mute on default audio sink <pre><code>// Set volume to 50%
send({cmd: 'vol_set', data: 50});

// Toggle mute
send({cmd: 'vol_mute'});
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>bri_set</code> <code>number</code> (0-100) Set screen brightness <code>toggle_night</code> -- Toggle night light (wlsunset) <pre><code>// Set brightness to 80%
send({cmd: 'bri_set', data: 80});

// Toggle night light
send({cmd: 'toggle_night'});
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>ws_go</code> <code>number</code> Switch to workspace by index <code>focus_window</code> <code>number</code> Focus window by ID <code>close_window</code> <code>number</code> Close window by ID <code>move_to_workspace</code> <code>{id, ws}</code> Move window to workspace <pre><code>// Switch to workspace 3
send({cmd: 'ws_go', data: 3});

// Focus window with id 42
send({cmd: 'focus_window', data: 42});

// Close window with id 42
send({cmd: 'close_window', data: 42});

// Move window 42 to workspace 2
send({cmd: 'move_to_workspace', data: {id: 42, ws: 2}});
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>wifi_con</code> <code>string</code> (SSID) Connect to WiFi network <code>wifi_dis</code> -- Disconnect WiFi <pre><code>// Connect to a network
send({cmd: 'wifi_con', data: 'HomeNetwork'});

// Disconnect
send({cmd: 'wifi_dis'});
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>toggle_dnd</code> -- Toggle Do Not Disturb mode <code>notif_dismiss</code> -- Dismiss all notifications (mako) <code>notif_dismiss_one</code> -- Dismiss latest notification (mako) <code>notif_clear_all</code> -- Clear all notifications from state <pre><code>// Toggle DND
send({cmd: 'toggle_dnd'});

// Dismiss all notifications via mako
send({cmd: 'notif_dismiss'});

// Clear notification list from Pulpkit state
send({cmd: 'notif_clear_all'});
</code></pre> <p><code>notif_dismiss</code> vs <code>notif_clear_all</code></p> <p><code>notif_dismiss</code> tells mako to dismiss notifications. <code>notif_clear_all</code> clears the <code>s.notifications</code> array and resets <code>s.notif_count</code> in Pulpkit's internal state. You typically want both.</p>

Command Data Description <code>set_profile</code> <code>string</code> Set power profile: <code>"balanced"</code>, <code>"performance"</code>, or <code>"power-saver"</code> <code>power_lock</code> -- Lock the session <code>power_suspend</code> -- Suspend the system <code>power_reboot</code> -- Reboot the system <code>power_shutdown</code> -- Shut down the system <code>power_logout</code> -- Log out (niri quit) <pre><code>// Set power profile
send({cmd: 'set_profile', data: 'performance'});

// Lock screen
send({cmd: 'power_lock'});

// Reboot
send({cmd: 'power_reboot'});
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>launch</code> <code>string</code> Launch application by exec command <code>exec</code> <code>string</code> Run arbitrary shell command <pre><code>// Launch Firefox
send({cmd: 'launch', data: 'firefox'});

// Run a shell command
send({cmd: 'exec', data: 'notify-send "Hello"'});
</code></pre> <p>launch vs exec</p> <p><code>launch</code> also dismisses the popup after launching. Use it for app launcher panels. <code>exec</code> runs the command silently without UI side effects.</p>

Command Data Description <code>popup</code> <code>string</code> Toggle a popup panel by name <code>dismiss</code> -- Close any open popup <pre><code>// Open settings panel (or close if already open)
send({cmd: 'popup', data: 'settings'});

// Close whatever popup is open
send({cmd: 'dismiss'});
</code></pre> <p>The <code>popup</code> command toggles: if the named panel is already open, it closes. Standard panel names are <code>settings</code>, <code>wifi</code>, <code>power</code>, <code>launcher</code>, and <code>config</code>, but you can use any string for custom panels.</p> <p>Special popup behavior</p> <p>Opening <code>wifi</code> triggers a WiFi network scan. Opening <code>launcher</code> scans installed applications. The results appear in <code>s.wifi_nets</code> and <code>s.apps</code> on the next state push.</p>

Command Data Description <code>set_custom</code> <code>{key, value}</code> Store a custom key-value pair in state <pre><code>// Set a custom value
send({cmd: 'set_custom', data: {key: 'sidebar_open', value: true}});

// Read it back in updateState:
// s.custom.sidebar_open === true
</code></pre>

Command Data Description <code>tray_activate</code> <code>{address, click}</code> Activate a system tray item <pre><code>// Left-click a tray item
send({cmd: 'tray_activate', data: {address: ':1.100', click: 'left'}});

// Right-click a tray item
send({cmd: 'tray_activate', data: {address: ':1.100', click: 'right'}});
</code></pre> <p>The <code>address</code> comes from <code>s.tray_items[].address</code>.</p>

Command Data Description <code>verify_password</code> <code>string</code> Verify password via PAM <code>unlock</code> -- Unlock the session <pre><code>// Submit password for verification
send({cmd: 'verify_password', data: passwordInput.value});

// After s.custom.auth_result === true, unlock
send({cmd: 'unlock'});
</code></pre> <p>See the lock screen guide for the full authentication flow.</p>

